HEADWORD: Tetanomotor
<hw>Tet`a*no*mo"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument from tetanizing a muscle by
irritating its nerve by successive mechanical shocks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

